  "description": "Karl (Kalle) Oskar Eklund was a Swedish artist born on July 13, 1891 in Örebro to Ernst E. and Karin Forsberg. He debuted in Stockholm in 1917 and his work is represented in the National Museum, Örebro Museum, Norrköping Museum and Linköping Museum. Karl was married to Maria Welin in 1920, and they had three children together: Karl-Göran, Kajsa and Ulla. Karl studied at Althin's School of Painting and the Royal Academy of Fine Arts in Stockholm. He also traveled to Denmark, Germany, the Netherlands, Belgium, France, and Italy for study purposes."
